	<item>
		<title>What is the difference between porcelain and ceramic tiles?</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[marbure_admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Porcelain tiles are denser and less porous than ceramic, making them more durable and better suited to high-traffic areas and outdoor use. Ceramic tiles are lighter, easier to cut, and typically more affordable, making them ideal for wall applications and lower-traffic floors.]]></content:encoded>
		<wp:post_type>marbure_faq</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_name>porcelain-vs-ceramic</wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>publish</wp:status>
		<wp:menu_order>1</wp:menu_order>
	</item>

	<item>
		<title>Do you offer a professional installation service?</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[marbure_admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Yes. Our experienced team of tilers can handle projects of any size, from single bathroom renovations to large commercial installations. We provide a full service from design consultation through to final grouting and finishing.]]></content:encoded>
