	<item>
		<title>How do I calculate how many tiles I need?</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[marbure_admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Measure the length and width of your room in metres and multiply them to get the floor area in square metres. We recommend adding 10% to account for cuts and breakages. Our showroom team can also help you calculate quantities when you visit or get in touch for a quote.]]></content:encoded>
		<wp:post_type>marbure_faq</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_name>how-many-tiles</wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>publish</wp:status>
		<wp:menu_order>3</wp:menu_order>
	</item>

	<item>
		<title>Are your outdoor tiles frost-proof?</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[marbure_admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[All of our outdoor porcelain tiles, including the Slate Grey Patio range, are manufactured to be frost-proof and suitable for year-round outdoor use in the UK climate. Check the product specification sheet for the specific frost resistance rating.]]></content:encoded>
