	</item>

	<item>
		<title>How to Choose the Right Grout for Your Tiles</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[marbure_admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Grout is often an afterthought, but the wrong choice can undermine even the most beautiful tile installation. Here's what to consider when selecting grout for your project.</p><h2>Matching vs. Contrasting Grout</h2><p>Matching grout colour to your tile creates a seamless effect, while contrasting grout (like dark grout on white tiles) makes a design statement and defines the tile pattern.</p><h2>Joint Width</h2><p>The width of your grout joint affects which grout type to use. Narrow joints (under 3mm) require unsanded grout; wider joints need sanded grout for strength.</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[The right grout makes or breaks a tile installation. Here's our guide to choosing colour, type, and joint width.]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_type>post</wp:post_type>
